# 3.3.blueprint.patent

structure the patent application.

---

## document structure

```
1. title
2. cross-reference to related applications (if any)
3. field of invention
4. background
   - prior art
   - problems in the art
5. summary
6. brief description of figures
7. detailed description
   - overview
   - embodiment 1
   - embodiment 2
   - variations
8. claims
9. abstract
10. figures
```

---

## title

<!-- 500 chars max, descriptive but not limiting -->



---

## field of invention

<!-- one paragraph, technical area -->



---

## background

### prior art summary

<!-- what was known before your invention -->



### problems in the art

<!-- what problems remained unsolved -->



---

## summary of invention

<!-- concise description of the invention and its advantages -->



---

## figures

| fig | description | shows |
|-----|-------------|-------|
| 1 | | |
| 2 | | |
| 3 | | |

---

## detailed description outline

### overview

<!-- high-level architecture -->

### embodiment 1 (preferred)

<!-- most important implementation -->

### embodiment 2 (alternative)

<!-- backup implementation -->

### variations

<!-- optional features, alternatives -->

---

## claims checklist

- [ ] claims match detailed description
- [ ] all claim elements supported by specification
- [ ] dependent claims provide fallback
- [ ] claim scope aligned with business goals

---

## abstract

<!-- 150 words max, standalone summary -->



---

## review checklist

- [ ] title is descriptive
- [ ] background establishes problem
- [ ] claims are supported
- [ ] figures are referenced
- [ ] no new matter in claims
- [ ] consistent terminology throughout

